
[1]thredbare

   THRED'BARE, a. [thread and bare.] Worn to the naked thread; having the
   nap worn off; as a threadbare coat; threadbare clothes.

   1. Worn out; trite; hackneyed; used till it has lost its novelty or
   interest; as a threadbare subject; state topics and threadbare
   quotations.
